"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-team-south-africa-latest-news-chad-le-clos-shrugs-off-injury-concerns-breaking\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbTeam SA news: Chad le Clos shrugs off injury concerns  South Africa's most decorated Olympian, Chad le Clos, has arrived at the athletes' village at the Paris\\u00a0Olympics 2024.  South Africa's most decorated Olympian,Chad le Clos, has arrived at the athletes' village at the Paris\\u00a0Olympics 2024 ready to make the most of his fourth experience at the greatest show on earth.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section  Le Clos joins only five other athletes to have done that in the country's history.  His four medals, one gold and three silver, are also the most of any South African Olympian, while he has a list\\u00a0of short-course achievements that could fill a library, making him one of the greatest swimmers the country has produced.  Now 32, he is taking to the water in the100m butterflyand admits that he has a lot to do.  \\\"I am the third oldest male swimmer at these Games, so in those terms I am something of a pensioner. And in spite of picking up a shoulder tear in training, I have come to Paris believing I have a chance. I have raced with injuries before.\\\"  Le Clos is a leader and a racer and although the odds seem to be against him adding to his medals tally in Paris, one also needs to acknowledge that if he gets to the final it's game on.  \\\"I think that the semi-final will be the harder race, because there will be 16 swimmers going for a place in the final. I am hoping to get there and once I do I will be chasing another dream. I am a warrior, a born racer.\\\"  Chad le Clos appeared toplay down the severity of his injuryat a media conference.  \\\"Yes, I have had an injury the last two weeks. I went to the medical team as soon as I arrived from Montpellier and had it checked out. The first thing I did after that was head for the dining hall!  \\\"I am here to enjoy the experience, even if I do not think it's my last, and give of my best.\\\"  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"